Define dependencies: `streamlit`, `pandas`, `numpy`, `opencv-python`, `scikit-learn`, `scipy`, `PyWavelets`, `plotly`, `reportlab`, `shap`, `imbalanced-learn`, `neurokit2`, `xgboost`, `lightgbm`.

### Shared Utilities
#### [NEW] [src/preprocessing.py](file:///d:/OneDrive/Documents/Placement_Preparation/Projects/Healthmonitoring_system/src/preprocessing.py)
- `apply_kalman_filter`: SciPy/custom Kalman filter implementation.
- `apply_wavelet_denoise`: Denoise signal using `PyWavelets`.
- `apply_bandpass_filter`: 0.5-40Hz filtering via `scipy.signal`.
- `scale_data`: Fit/transform `StandardScaler`.
- `apply_smote`: `SMOTE` implementation from `imblearn` for training.

#### [NEW] [src/feature_engineering.py](file:///d:/OneDrive/Documents/Placement_Preparation/Projects/Healthmonitoring_system/src/feature_engineering.py)
- `extract_hr_features`: Pipeline using Wavelet (db6, level 5-6), Bandpass (0.8-3.5Hz, 4th order Butterworth), Normalization, and fused peak-finding (distance=fs*0.3) + FFT (0.8-3Hz max peak) with continuity checks.
- `extract_spo2_features`: Bandpass (0.7-4Hz), calculate AC (signal-DC) and DC (low-pass < 0.5Hz or rolling mean) for Red/Green channels. Compute R = (AC/DC_red) / (AC/DC_green). Extract using LightGBM/XGBoost regressor or linear calibration.
- `extract_ecg_features`: Use `neurokit2.signal.ecg_process()` for cleaning, peak detection, and HRV. Normalize RR intervals (Hampel filter) and include frequency-domain HRV (LF/HF ratio via Welch PSD).

### Machine Learning
#### [NEW] [src/model.py](file:///d:/OneDrive/Documents/Placement_Preparation/Projects/Healthmonitoring_system/src/model.py)
- `TriBoostEnsemble(BaseEstimator)`: Ensemble classifier combining 3 boosting models (e.g., XGBoost, LightGBM, CatBoost or RF/GBM/AdaBoost depending on installed libraries, defaulting to `scikit-learn` variants if avoiding external C++ boosters).
- `train_model()`: Pipeline compiling preprocessing -> model fitting.

#### [NEW] [src/inference.py](file:///d:/OneDrive/Documents/Placement_Preparation/Projects/Healthmonitoring_system/src/inference.py)
- `predict_risk()`: Loads trained `TriBoostEnsemble` and runs `predict_proba`.
- `get_shap_values()`: Initializes `shap.TreeExplainer` on the model and returns SHAP values.

